$ VBA statement: open
@ open

`open` can be used to open a file for reading or writing.

Use → development/languages/VBA/functions#freeFile to determine the next »file descriptor« for `open`.


{ open for output

  gh|about-VBA|/language/statements/open/open-for-output.bas||

}

sa:

  The → development/languages/VBA/language/statements/print[`print#`] statement.

  The `open` statement and → development/languages/VBA/language/statements/open/character-encoding[character encodings]

  → development/languages/VBA/Win-API/examples/GetTempFileName[GetTempFileName] to create a name for temporary files.

  The functions in the → development/languages/VBA/modules/Common/File[`File` module], especially `slurpFile` (which reads an entire file
  into a → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/string[string]) and its corresponding `flushToFile`.

  → development/languages/VBA/language/statements
